  "stimulus": "For t (cid:149) 0, a particle is moving along a curve so that its position at time t is (cid:11)x(cid:11)t(cid:12), y(cid:11)t(cid:12)(cid:12). At time t (cid:32) 2, the\nparticle is at position (cid:11)1,5(cid:12). It is known that dx (cid:32) t (cid:14) 2 and dy (cid:32) sin2t.\ndt et dt",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "Is the horizontal movement of the particle to the left or to the right at time t (cid:32) 2? Explain your answer.\nFind the slope of the path of the particle at time t (cid:32) 2.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct direction (to the right) with reason based on sign of dx/dt",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$dx/dt|_{t=2} = 2/e^4 > 0$, so moving to the right"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct slope of path at t = 2",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$dy/dx = (dy/dt)/(dx/dt)$ at $t = 2$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\frac{dy}{dx}\\big|_{t=2} \\approx 3.055$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct chain rule setup for dy/dx",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$dy/dx = (dy/dt)/(dx/dt)$ with both derivatives computed"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "Find the x-coordinate of the particle’s position at time t (cid:32) 4.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct integral setup for x-coordinate at t = 4",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$x(4) = x(2) + \\int_2^4 x'(t)\\, dt$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$x(4) = 1 + \\int_2^4 \\frac{t}{e^{t+2}}\\, dt \\approx 1.032$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct x(4) value",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Uses initial condition $x(2) = 1$",
                "Correct numerical answer"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$x(4) \\approx 1.032$ or $1.033$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "Find the speed of the particle at time t (cid:32) 4. Find the acceleration vector of the particle at time t (cid:32) 4.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "c1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct speed at t = 4",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Speed $= \\sqrt{(x'(4))^2 + (y'(4))^2}$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\approx 1.484$"
            }
          ],
          "common_traps": [
            "Computing velocity vector instead of speed (must take magnitude)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct acceleration vector at t = 4",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\langle x''(4), y''(4) \\rangle$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\langle -0.012, -2.619 \\rangle$ (or $\\langle -0.013, -2.620 \\rangle$)"
            }
          ],
          "common_traps": [
            "Reporting scalar acceleration instead of vector"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "d",
      "prompt": "Find the distance traveled by the particle from time t (cid:32) 2 to t (cid:32) 4.",
      "point_value": 2,
